n unnamed user classes without needing add-opens. If the tests don't interact with Object.class methods or java.lang.String internals, that shouldn't be necessary. However, I should question the need for existing add-opens—perhaps they relate to previously generated tests, but can I achieve meaningful coverage without them?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL 3.3.5 is a local expression/reflection library; its only runtime dependency, Javassist 3.29.0-GA, is already a transitive dependency of ognl:ognl:3.3.5. Normal meaningful tests can exercise parsing, get/set, method calls, constructors, static members, maps, arrays, and expression compilation without Docker, extra Maven dependencies, or mandatory environment/system properties. The reported java-run failure is a test expectation/behavior change in ObjectPropertyAccessor, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OGNL has optional system properties such as ognl.security.manager, ognl.UseJDK9PlusAccessHandler, ognl.UseStricterInvocation, and ognl.UseFirstMatchGetSetLookup, but these are feature toggles, not prerequisites for ordinary coverage.\",\n    \"SecurityManager-focused tests are fragile on modern JDKs and should be guarded or avoided unless specifically validating OGNL sandbox behavior.\",\n    \"Javassist-backed expression compilation may have native-image limitations, but the dependency is resolved transitively and does not require an extra deterministic setup entry.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c0ae6e47a3df1b2016a4123dfbd348190afec55795e761ad6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3609, "output": 784, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33577, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 178265390